Sentencas: Here, stability of the metal-supported solid oxide fuel cell (MS-SOFC) with Ni-Ce0,8Sm0,202_6 (SDC) infiltrated 430L anode and La(0.6)Sro(4)Fe(0.9)Sc(0.1)O(3-delta) (LSFSc) infiltrated scandia-stabilized zirconia (SSZ) cathode is evaluated.
Titulo: Long-term stability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells employing infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: It is found that the degradation rate defined as the voltage loss during a fixed period is faster at higher operation temperatures and larger current densities.
Titulo: Long-term stability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells employing infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) and energy dispersive X-ray spectra (EDS) analysis indicate that the degradation is mainly caused by the morphological change of the anode while metal element diffusion between Ni catalyst and 430L substrate contributes little.
Titulo: Long-term stability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells employing infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: A 1500 h durability test measured at 650 degrees C and 0.9 A cm(-2) shows a degradation rate of 1.3% kh(-1) and the voltage decrease is mainly found in the initial 500 h. (C) 2015
Titulo: Long-term stability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells employing infiltrated electrodes
